SouthCap offers to buy United Home . Life insurance holding company SouthCap Corp said Tuesday it had offered to buy United Home Life Insurance Co at a cash price of $ 4 . 50 a share . SouthCap said its offer , which will expire on May 20 , was subject to it receiving at least 50 . 1 percent of United Home ' s outstanding common stock . It said it would use " available resources " to finance the offer . SouthCap said it already owned 3 . 6 percent of United Home Life and held the right to buy another 2 . 8 percent . United Home , an Indiana insurance company , has about 1 . 2 million shares , it added . An official at United Home said the insurer deemed the offering price to be too low . " Our management considers it to be below what the company is worth , " he said . 
